# API Rules

## The proxy pattern
All frontend API calls go through Next.js API routes at `/api/proxy/[...path]`.
This proxy forwards requests to the real backend and injects the auth token server-side.

**Frontend component → `@eduforge/api-client` → `/api/proxy/...` → Real Backend**

Never call the backend URL directly from client components. The backend URL is only ever read in `apps/web/src/app/api/proxy/[...path]/route.ts`.

## TanStack Query patterns

### Queries (reading data)
```typescript
// In _hooks/use-courses.ts
export function useCourses(tenantId: string) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['courses', tenantId],
    queryFn: () => coursesApi.list(tenantId),
    enabled: !!tenantId,
  })
}
```

### Mutations (writing data)
```typescript
export function useCreateCourse() {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient()
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: coursesApi.create,
    onSuccess: (_, variables) => {
      void queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['courses', variables.tenantId] })
    },
  })
}
```

## Query keys convention
Always use arrays. Structure: `[resource, id?, filter?]`
- `['courses', tenantId]`
- `['course', courseId]`
- `['agencies']`
- `['agency', agencyId]`
- `['builder-page', pageId]`

## Server-side data fetching
In Server Components, call `@eduforge/api-client` functions directly.
Pass the auth token from the session.
Never use `useQuery` in Server Components.
